              <a name=
              "id2486375" id="id2486375">What is tovid?==





tovid is a collection
        of video disc authoring tools; it can help you create your
        own DVDs, VCDs, and SVCDs for playback on your home DVD
        player. It has a <a href="#cli" title=
        "Using the command-line tools">command-line interface
        as well as a [graphical frontend #gui]. tovid is <a href=
        "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_software" target=
        "_top">free software.


You may find tovid useful if:



            - 

you have a digital camcorder, and want to share
              home movies with family and friends


            - 

you are a 3D artist or animator, and want to put
              your portfolio on DVD for easy distribution


            - 

your video files are eating up too much hard drive
              space, and you want to back them up onto a portable
              medium







Interested? See <a href="#getting_started" title=
        "Getting started">Getting started for download and
        installation instructions.






